article.description: Jeremy Senglin scored 26 points and Joel Bolomboy added 20 points and pulled down a career-high 23 rebounds as Weber State took an early lead and ran with it to take a 74-62 win over North Dakota
article.headline: Senglin, Bolomboy lead Weber State past North Dakota, 74-62
article.linkText: Senglin, Bolomboy lead Weber State past North Dakota, 74-62
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Jeremy Senglin scored 26 points and Joel Bolomboy added 20 points and pulled down a career-high 23 rebounds as Weber State took an early lead and ran with it to take a 74-62 win over North Dakota Thursday night. Senglin was 7 of 11 from the field and 5-of-11 shooting from distance. Bolomboy collected his 14th double-double in 15 games this the season by hitting 8 of 14 shots from the field and pulling down 10 caroms off the offensive glass to go with 13 defensive rebounds. The win is the fifth straight for the Wildcats (10-5, 2-0 Big Sky), who are now 8-0 all-time against North Dakota. Quinton Hooker scored 23 points off the bench to lead North Dakota(6-8, 1-2), shooting 6 of 16 from the field and 10 of 11 from the free-throw line. He was the lone Fighting Hawk to reach double-figure scoring.
